Title: SAIHV-Genomic: A Deterministic Framework for Autonomous AI Orchestration

Abstract:
Modern AI architectures often suffer from "Monolithic Bloat" and excessive discovery latency when deployed across heterogeneous hardware substrates. SAIHV-Genomic is an architectural design pattern that addresses these challenges by refactoring AI logic from heavy, script-based dependencies into Atomic Gene-Packets.

Key Technical Features:

The Genomic-Atomic Standard: Encapsulates system traits into immutable, compressed JSON instruction sets, ensuring zero "system-drift" and 100% deterministic execution.

Zero-Probe Injection (ZPI): Replaces hardware discovery with cached profile-based instantiation, achieving <5ms Time-To-First-Thought (TFT) latency.

Autonomous Governance: Implements a reactive, self-policing architectural layer that prevents the accumulation of legacy code through automated structural refactoring.

Substrate-Agnostic Fabric: Decouples logic from hardware, allowing a single AI core to maintain 1:1 hardware equilibrium across edge, mobile, and server-grade environments.

Value Proposition:
This framework provides a path to exponential computational efficiency, reducing overhead and maintenance complexity while ensuring high-reliability, deterministic performance for autonomous agentic systems.
